title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return recognizable strings
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, the returned value does not contain recognizable strings.
EB: IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return user recognizable strings regardless of when it is called.
SR: Ensure that IMetaData.getColumnLabel() consistently returns recognizable strings from the meta data object, regardless of when it is called.
